<h2>Overview</h2>

<p>My home lab is a collection of diverse hardware spanning multiple decades and architectures. It serves as a testing ground for experiments, a learning environment, and a reminder of computing history. From vintage PowerPC and MIPS systems to modern x86 servers, each machine has its purpose and story.</p>

<h2>Hardware Inventory</h2>

<h3>Vintage Systems</h3>

<p>The vintage systems in my lab represent different eras and philosophies of computing. They're not just museum pieces; many are still functional and occasionally used for specific tasks or testing.</p>

